      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;using-images-in-blog-posts&#34;&gt;Using Images in Blog Posts&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can add images to your posts in two ways:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using regular markdown syntax:
&lt;img alt=&#34;Go Gopher&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/static/images/gopher.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using HTML for more control:
&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/static/images/gopher.png&#34; alt=&#34;Go Gopher&#34; style=&#34;max-width: 300px; border-radius: 8px;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Images can be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PNG, JPG, GIF formats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Placed in the static/images directory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Referenced using relative paths&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;youtube video embedding:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&amp;v=nTQUwghvy5Q&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;
 &lt;img src=&#34;http://img.youtube.com/vi/nTQUwghvy5Q/mqdefault.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Watch the video&#34; width=&#34;240&#34; height=&#34;180&#34; border=&#34;10&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;</description>
